    "The temporal attention mechanism is shown in Fig. 6c.",
    "In our work, the output vector H att, which is obtained through the temporal attention mechanism in TA-LSTM, is the weighted sum of all states in H {h t-3, h t-2, h t-1 h t }.",
    "The temporal attention weight β and attention mechanism output H att can be defined as follows:",
    "Compared with LSTM, the difference with TA-LSTM lies in the post-processing of the LSTM output.",
    "LSTM utilizes the last hidden state output for prediction, whereas TA-LSTM employs temporal weighting to utilize all hidden state outputs."
